                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d170">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.20/7–1449: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in the United Kingdom</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-15T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 15, 1949—8 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2476. Dept fully concurs recommendation your 2754, July 14 (532 to Paris) that
                    you should approach Bevin after Senate has completed action on Pact re obtaining
                    agreement for US observers to attend mtgs Permanent Commission. Agreeable that
                    observer be Executive Director <gloss target="#t_ECC1">ECC</gloss> when
                    appointed. In actual operation this will have to be handled so as not to give
                    cause to non-<gloss target="#t_WU1">WU</gloss> Atlantic Pact countries for
                    suspicion that we are minimizing their interest by concentration on <gloss
                        target="#t_WU1">WU</gloss> activities. Believe this can be satisfactorily
                    handled by relationship established between Executive Director of <gloss
                        target="#t_ECC1">ECC</gloss>, our Ambassadors and representatives of such
                    countries.</p>
                <p>Department concurs your paragraph 3 that at an appropriate time you should raise
                    question of your sitting with Consultative Council when discussing matters of
                    interest to US. Department agreeable to leaving timing to you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
